      "body": "I just tried the same in the console window of the Qt app and it's even worse.  In there the input buffer stops accepting input at 32767 characters.  So I don't see any way at all of decoding the transaction to gain access to the `scriptPubKey` of the transaction output that was sent to me.\n\nI guess I could just use `listunspent`, since that includes the `scriptPubKey`.\n",
